HEADWORD: change-of-pace
<hw>change-of-pace</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Baseball)</fld> <def>a
baseball pitch thrown with little velocity when the batter is expecting
a fastball; -- called also <altname>change-up</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> change-up, change-of-pace ball, off-speed
pitch.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

